WASHINGTON (AP) - House Speaker John Boehner has scheduled the House election to replace him for Oct. 29 and delayed votes for lower-level posts until after that. House Republicans had planned to vote Thursday by secret ballot for a new leadership team. But a number of members wanted more time to weigh their options and pursue rule changes amid general disarray in the aftermath of Boehner's sudden resignation.
